# Layout Architecture Guidelines

## Core Layout System

The application uses a centralized layout system managed by [ConditionalLayout.tsx](mdc:components/ConditionalLayout.tsx) which:

- Manages the sidebar structure with [Sidebar.tsx](mdc:components/Sidebar.tsx)
- Applies base styling (`bg-gray-50`, `p-6 pt-16 lg:pt-6`) to main content
- Handles responsive design and mobile adaptations
- Determines when to show/hide the sidebar based on routes

## Layout Rules

### ❌ DO NOT
- Use `min-h-screen` in page components (already handled by ConditionalLayout)
- Use `max-w-7xl` or other max-width containers (conflicts with sidebar layout)
- Apply `bg-gray-50` or similar background colors (already applied)
- Create full-page layouts that ignore the existing structure

### ✅ DO
- Use negative margins (`-m-6`, `-mx-6`) to extend elements to full width
- Apply corresponding padding (`p-6`, `px-6`) when using negative margins
- Use `sticky top-0` for navigation elements that should stick to top
- Leverage the existing padding structure for consistent spacing

## Example Pattern

```tsx
// Good: Working with ConditionalLayout
<div className="space-y-0">
  {/* Full-width header */}
  <div className="bg-white shadow-sm -m-6 mb-0 p-6">
    <Header />
  </div>
  
  {/* Full-width sticky navigation */}
  <div className="bg-white border-b border-gray-200 sticky top-0 z-10 -mx-6 px-6">
    <Navigation />
  </div>
  
  {/* Content with standard padding */}
  <div className="pt-6">
    <Content />
  </div>
</div>
```

